article.headline: Siena 68, Holy Cross 63
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- David Ryan and Tay Fisher scored 18 points apiece to lead Siena to a 68-63 win over Holy Cross Thursday night. Kojo Mensah added 12 points for the Saints (2-2), while Antoine Jordan had 10 points and 13 rebounds. Siena jumped out to a 12-2 lead in the first half, but Holy Cross (2-4) responded with a 7-0 run and trailed 26-24 at halftime. After a 29-29 tie, the Saints used an 8-0 run to take control and led by as many as 15 points in the second half. The Crusaders made it a four-point game with 54.7 seconds left but had a turnover on their next possession. Siena shot 37 percent from the field but made 10-of-22 from 3-point range. Keith Simmons led Holy Cross with 20 points and Colin Cunningham contributed 16. Torey Thomas had 11 rebounds.
